    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-23T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/247</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-23T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1916, 11 a. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 25, 9.20 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>455. Swiss Minister for Foreign Affairs, in giving me a copy of the note<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d160fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_117">p. 117</ref>.</note>
                    which the Swiss Federal Council has presented to each of the belligerent powers,
                    a copy of which has been forwarded to the President through the Swiss Minister
                    at Washington, states that the Federal Council has decided to extend its most
                    enthusiastic support <pb facs="0399" n="113" xml:id="pg_113"/> to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s note regarding peace. The
                    Federal Council has decided upon this action unanimously and the Minister added
                    that in forwarding its note to the belligerents the Federal Council had not in
                    mind a collective action or representation with the President. Its purpose is to
                    show to the belligerent nations that the point of view of the oldest as well as
                    of the greatest republic of the world in regard to peace is the same.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
